)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/macs_qc_summary.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Db9aXoLdKg0UxEAx3zD0pSTT", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R library `dplyr` for data manipulation.\\n2. Define a function `compute_summary` to read a narrowPeak file, calculate peak length, and compute summary statistics for `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`, `-log10(pvalue)`, and `length`.\\n3. Use the `compute_summary` function to process each of the three input files: `sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak`, `sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak`, and `sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak`.\\n4. Combine the summary statistics from all samples into a single data frame.\\n5. Write the combined summary statistics to `output/macs_qc_summary.tsv` using `write.table` with specified parameters.\\n6. Verify the output file is correctly generated and contains the expected data.\\n7. Submit the task as complete if the output file is correct.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (752 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_Db9aXoLdKg0UxEAx3zD0pSTT"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_WKHuwV61uf70sipp17LWYNVu", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(dplyr)\\n\\ncompute_summary <- function(file_path, sample_name) {\\n  data <- read.table(file_path, header = FALSE, sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\")\\n  colnames(data) <- c(\\\"chr\\\", \\\"start\\\", \\\"end\\\", \\\"name\\\", \\\"score\\\", \\\"strand\\\", \\\"fold\\\", \\\"pvalue\\\", \\\"qvalue\\\", \\\"peak\\\")\\n  data$length <- data$end - data$start\\n  summary_stats <- data %>%\\n    summarise(\\n      num_peaks = n(),\\n      fold_min = min(fold),\\n      fold_1st_qu = quantile(fold, 0.25),\\n      fold_median = median(fold),\\n      fold_mean = mean(fold),\\n      fold_3rd_qu = quantile(fold, 0.75),\\n      fold_max = max(fold),\\n      qvalue_min = min(-log10(qvalue)),\\n      qvalue_1st_qu = quantile(-log10(qvalue), 0.25),\\n      qvalue_median = median(-log10(qvalue)),\\n      qvalue_mean = mean(-log10(qvalue)),\\n      qvalue_3rd_qu = quantile(-log10(qvalue), 0.75),\\n      qvalue_max = max(-log10(qvalue)),\\n      pvalue_min = min(-log10(pvalue)),\\n      pvalue_1st_qu = quantile(-log10(pvalue), 0.25),\\n      pvalue_median = median(-log10(pvalue)),\\n      pvalue_mean = mean(-log10(pvalue)),\\n      pvalue_3rd_qu = quantile(-log10(pvalue), 0.75),\\n      pvalue_max = max(-log10(pvalue)),\\n      length_min = min(length),\\n      length_1st_qu = quantile(length, 0.25),\\n      length_median = median(length),\\n      length_mean = mean(length),\\n      length_3rd_qu = quantile(length, 0.75),\\n      length_max = max(length)\\n    ) %>%\\n    mutate(sample = sample_name)\\n  return(summary_stats)\\n}\\n\\nsummary_A <- compute_summary(\\\"input/sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\\\", \\\"sampleA\\\")\\nsummary_B <- compute_summary(\\\"input/sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\\\", \\\"sampleB\\\")\\nsummary_C <- compute_summary(\\\"input/sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\\\", \\\"sampleC\\\")\\n\\nsummary.dat <- bind_rows(summary_A, summary_B, summary_C)\\n\\nwrite.table(summary.dat, \\\"output/macs_qc_summary.tsv\\\", sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\", row.names = FALSE, col.names = TRUE, quote = FALSE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool"